Maintainer: Hossein Haghbin <haghbin@pgu.ac.ir>
Description: Methods and tools for implementing multivariate hybrid principal component analysis ('MHPCA') for multivariate (non)functional data whose variables might be observed over different dimensional domains. 'MHPCA' is an object-oriented interface leveraging the extensibility and scalability of R6. It employs a parameter vector to control the smoothness of each functional variable. By incorporating smoothness constraints as penalty terms within a regularized optimization framework, 'MHPCA' generates smooth multivariate (non)functional principal components, offering a concise and interpretable representation of the data. For detailed information on the methods and techniques used in 'MHPCA', please refer to Mahmoudiandehkordi et al. (2025) <doi:10.48550/arXiv.xxxx.yyyyy>. 
